references.paper_title: Break-a-scene: Extracting multiple concepts from a single image
references.reason: This paper introduces a novel method for extracting multiple concepts from a single image, which is highly relevant to the task of fine-grained 3D object generation.

references.paper_title: Dreamavatar: Text-and-shape guided 3d human avatar generation via diffusion models
references.reason: This paper presents a method for generating high-quality 3D human avatars, which is relevant to the paper's goal of generating high-quality 3D bird models.

references.paper_title: Emerging properties in self-supervised vision transformers
references.reason: This paper introduces a novel self-supervised learning approach for training vision transformers, which is relevant to the paper's approach of using self-supervised learning to improve visual coherency.
This paper introduces ShapeNet, a large-scale dataset of 3D models, which is used as a benchmark for evaluating 3D object generation methods.

references.paper_title: LoRA: Low-rank adaptation of large language models
references.reason: This paper introduces LoRA, a novel method for adapting large language models, which is used in the paper to improve the efficiency of training the 3D bird generation model.
